article.description: Sean Hoehn had 31 points as Sacred Heart routed Robert Morris 87-63 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Hoehn lifts Sacred Heart over Robert Morris 87-63
article.linkText: Hoehn lifts Sacred Heart over Robert Morris 87-63
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. -- Sean Hoehn had 31 points as Sacred Heart routed Robert Morris 87-63 on Thursday night. Hoehn hit 5 of 6 3-pointers. Koreem Ozier, who was second on the Pioneers in scoring coming into the matchup with 15 points per game, shot only 20 percent for the game (1 of 5). Charles Bain had 17 points for the Colonials (15-15, 10-7 Northeast Conference). Jon Williams added 12 points. Yannis Mendy had 10 points. Josh Williams, whose 14 points per game coming into the contest led the Colonials, shot only 17 percent for the game (1 of 6). The Pioneers leveled the season series against the Colonials with the win. Robert Morris defeated Sacred Heart 72-64 on Jan. 24. Sacred Heart (14-16, 10-7) finishes out the regular season against St. Francis (Pa.) at home on Saturday. Robert Morris finishes out the regular season against Wagner on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
